[1] Sri Lanka
Date: Wed 14 Jul 2010
Source: Daily News (Sri Lanka) [edited]
<http://www.dailynews.lk/2010/07/14/news41.asp>


During the last 6 months in Galle district, 408 dengue patients have
been identified, a Health Department official said. Last year [2009],
657 dengue patients were identified from the district, the official
said. Galle Municipality Health Services Director Dr Sriyani
Jayasuriya said arrangements have been made to bring the disease
under control. Dengue is fast spreading in Poddala-Bope, Ganegama,
Imaduwa and Hikkaduwa Divisional Secretariat areas, the officials said.

Meanwhile, a Health Ministry official said the number of dengue
patients in the island has risen to 18 611 this year [2010]. The
dengue death toll from January to July [2010] is 132.

[Byline: Richmond Wijesekera]

