[5] Viet Nam (Binh Duong)
Date: Tue 13 Jul 2010
Source: Radio the Voice of Vietnam (VOV) News [edited]
<http://english.vovnews.vn/Home/Dengue-fever-spreading-in-southern-Binh-Duong/20107/117419.vov>


Dengue fever is now rampant in many areas in southern province of
Binh Duong including Thuan An, Di An, Ben Cat, and Thu Dau Mot town.
To cope with the epidemic, the province has set up a quick-response
team to control outbreaks of dengue fever. The province has also
prepared medicine and equipment as well as chemicals to prevent the
spread of the disease.

Doctor Luong Thi Hong Le, director of the provincial preventive
health centre said the centre has run crash courses for medical staff
at grassroots level so that they can early detect and stamp out new outbreaks.

