[6] Thailand (national)
Date: Mon 12 Jul 2010
Source: National News Bureau of Thailand (NNT) [edited]
<http://thainews.prd.go.th/en/news.php?id=255307120022>


The Ministry of Public Health has assigned all provincial public
health offices nationwide to launch an all-out campaign against
dengue fever as the disease usually peaks during July-September.
Public Health Minister Jurin Laksanawisit said health workers had
been instructed to urgently eradicate mosquito spawning sites and
spray chemicals in community areas.

Mr Jurin expressed his concerns over the outbreak as a total of 33
113 people had already been infected with the mosquito-borne [virus]
disease since January 2010 while 33 patients died from the disease.
He elaborated that the number increased by 60 percent from last year [2009].

According to the minister, the majority of patients or about 11 440
people are found in the central region of the kingdom while the
figure for the southern part stands at 9035. As for the northeastern
and northern parts, the numbers of patients are lower at 8842 and
3756 respectively.

